name: Mount Ile Mandiri
description:
I caught this moment when I was on the Pelni ship on the way to Papua, Merauke in 2016.

this is the view of Mount Ile Mandiri from the sea. Mount Mandiri is an inactive volcano located in the easternmost part of Flores Island, East Flores Regency, East Nusa Tenggara Province, Indonesia.
 
Administratively this mountain is located on the border of Larantuka City with Ile Mandiri District in East Flores Regency.

Mount Ile Mandiri is believed to be the ancestor of the tribes that exist and are scattered around Larantuka City or at the foot of this mountain. It is not known when the volcano last erupted.

This mountain complex has experienced landslides and floods and became a major disaster in 1979 with the death toll reaching 96 people, 53 were declared missing and hundreds were injured.
